The article announces the nominations and appointments made by President Donald J. Trump for various positions. Joseph N. Mondello of New York has been nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary & Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Trinidad & Tobago. Stephen Akard of Indiana has been nominated to be the Director of the Office of Foreign Missions. Sharon Fast Gustafson of Virginia has been nominated to be the General Counsel of the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission. The article also mentions that President Trump has designated an individual to be the Chair of the Surface Transportation Board, but the name is not provided.